---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import PageHeader from '../../components/PageHeader.astro';
import SectionSubnav from '../../components/SectionSubnav.astro';
import { aboutSubnav } from '../../data/nav';
import Cta from '../../components/Cta.astro';
---
<Base title="Governance — Eight Hands Martial Arts Academy">
  <SectionSubnav items={aboutSubnav} active="/about/governance" label="About section" />
  <PageHeader eyebrow="About" title="Governance" subtitle="The standards that keep student development at the center." />
  <section class="bg-stone">
    <div class="container-content py-section-sm lg:py-section max-w-3xl space-y-5 reveal text-slate/90">
      <p class="text-lg">At Eight Hands Martial Arts Academy, every decision is guided by a simple principle: the needs and development of the student come first. Our programs, instructional methods, and educational pathways are designed to help students build confidence, discipline, focus, communication, leadership, and self-governance through consistent participation and purposeful practice.</p>
      <p>Governance at Eight Hands means maintaining clear standards for instruction, student progress, safety, and accountability. Students are evaluated according to their individual development rather than comparison with others. Instructors are expected to model the same principles we seek to cultivate in our students: professionalism, responsibility, continuous learning, and respect for the educational process.</p>
      <p>Progress is measured not only by technical skill, but by the student’s ability to apply what they learn in meaningful ways. We believe growth is best supported when expectations are clear, feedback is constructive, and students are encouraged to take ownership of their development. Through individualized instruction and regular review, we work to ensure that each student’s educational pathway remains aligned with their goals and long-term growth.</p>
      <p class="eyebrow !text-navy pt-6">Safeguarding and Accountability</p>
      <p>The wellbeing of our students is fundamental to everything we do. We are committed to providing an environment that is physically safe, emotionally supportive, and conducive to learning. All students are expected to be treated with dignity and respect, regardless of age, experience, background, or ability.</p>
      <p>We maintain clear policies regarding conduct, supervision, communication, and student welfare. Parents and students are encouraged to communicate openly with academy leadership, and concerns are addressed promptly and professionally. Accountability exists at every level of the academy, ensuring that expectations are consistent for students, instructors, and leadership alike.</p>
      <p>The purpose of governance is not control for its own sake. Its purpose is to create the structure, consistency, and trust necessary for meaningful development to occur. By maintaining high standards and a culture of accountability, we strive to provide an environment where students and families can pursue growth with confidence.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <Cta />
</Base>
